description:
&lt;p&gt;These posts are available as part of a service restructure to ensure there is an appropriate skill mix of Orthoptists to support complex orthoptic and ophthalmic services in addition to service expansion. In addition to the core orthoptic role there is a requirement for the successful candidates to undertake training for role developments, these may include, cyst minor ops lists, YAG capsulotomy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Orthoptic department at NUH offers clinical placements for orthoptic undergraduates, optometrists, medical students, post graduate medics and other health professionals and the post holder would be expected to contribute to this clinical teaching role and support other orthoptists in delivering their teaching responsibilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A Diploma/Degree in Orthoptics plus HcPC registration is required and experience as a clinical tutor would be advantageous. For further information, please contact Isabel Ash, Head Orthoptist or Victoria Jarvis, Deputy Head Orthoptist on 0115 9249924 ext 61750/65662; e-mail isabel.ash@nuh.nhs.uk or victoria.jarvis@nuh.nhs.uk &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As part of our commitment to provide the best care to our patients, we have extended services to include evening and weekend clinics. As a member of the Orthoptic team you will be expected to participate in the provision of these clinics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameIsabel AshJob titleHead OrthoptistEmail addressisabel.ash@nuh.nhs.ukTelephone number0115 9709750Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Isabel Ash, Head of Orthoptics, optometry and ophthalmic imaging or Victoria Jarvis, Deputy Head Orthoptist on 0115 9249924 ext 61750/61009;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;E-mail isabel.ash@nuh.nhs.uk or victoria.jarvis@nuh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
